  <context>
    <background>
      `CapabilityRouter` is a multi-layer cascade (Layer 1 keyword classifier → Layer 2 LLM disambiguator → Layer 3 fallback). The Layer-1 hit rate is 68.6% on the corpus (above the 60% target); Layer 2/3 corrects misroutes in live traffic. The bug observable only in isolated Layer-1 benchmark tests — production routing converges. However, the documented zero-false-positive invariant for Layer 1 is violated, which undermines single-call cost optimization for affected message patterns.

      The 3 fix options have very different scope characteristics: option 1 (~2h) is minimally invasive but only fixes the bigram-superstring class; option 2 (~4-6h) is comprehensive but may approach the 50% line replacement limit; option 3 (~1h) is the contract-guarantee fix but sacrifices Layer-1 hit rate.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="013" status="required">Phase 1 exit triple-run validated</dependency>
      <dependency task="owner-decision" status="required">Owner ACK on 3-option ranking before implementation</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Capabilities/CapabilityRouter.cs</file>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Capabilities/CapabilityRouterBenchmarkTests.cs</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Load RB-T053-01 ledger entry (lines 428-491 in real-bug-ledger.md). Confirm Status is `open` or `assigned-to-r2`.</step>
    <step order="2">🔔 **Human Input Required** — surface the 3 fix options to the owner with effort estimates + tradeoffs; recommend approach 2 if router precision matters for cost, approach 3 if the contract guarantee matters more. WAIT for owner ACK before proceeding.</step>
    <step order="3">Once owner selects: read `CapabilityRouter.cs` Layer-1 scoring path (the substring-match + confidence formula identified in the ledger). Hand-trace the failing assertions in `Layer1_DoesNotFalsePositive_OnNonKeywordMessages` test (line ~191) to confirm the bug reproduces.</step>
    <step order="4">Apply the selected fix option. For option 1 (word-boundary): swap `Contains(hint, OrdinalIgnoreCase)` for `Regex.IsMatch(message, $@"\b{Regex.Escape(hint)}\b", RegexOptions.IgnoreCase)`. For option 2: add a hint-subset map + discount; per-message scoring updated. For option 3: cap single-match confidence at 0.75 in the confidence formula.</step>
    <step order="5">Verify NFR-02: if option 2 is chosen and edits approach 50% line replacement on `CapabilityRouter.cs`, STOP and produce `escalations/rewrite-request-T-022-CapabilityRouter.md` before continuing.</step>
    <step order="6">Remove `Skip = "..."` + per-test traits on `Layer1_DoesNotFalsePositive_OnNonKeywordMessages` + `Layer1_FullCorpus_DistributionSummary`.</step>
    <step order="7">Build: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`. Verify 0 errors.</step>
    <step order="8">Run targeted tests: `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~CapabilityRouter"`. Confirm both Layer-1 tests pass + Layer 2/3 cascade tests remain green.</step>
    <step order="9">Step 9.5 quality gates: `code-review` + `adr-check`. Verify <50% line replacement (or escalation filed); no DI changes; AI service stays in-process.</step>
    <step order="10">Update RB-T053-01 ledger: Status → `repaired`; record chosen fix option in ledger Notes + decision record `decisions/D-08-rb-t053-01-fix-option.md`. Commit: `fix(ai/capabilities): apply Layer-1 false-positive fix option N to CapabilityRouter (RB-T053-01; repaired)`. Update `current-task.md`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">CapabilityRouter.cs + test file + ledger entry</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Production fix per chosen option + test Skip removal</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">`dotnet build` + targeted `dotnet test`</tool>
